definitions.definition: to send goods to another country for sale:
examples: French cheeses are exported to many different countries.

definitions.definition: to put something from one country into use in other countries:
examples: American culture has been exported all over the world.

definitions.definition: If you export information from a computer, you copy a large amount of it to a different part of the computer's memory or to another device.
a product that you sell in another country, or the business of sending goods to another country in order to sell them there:
examples: Coffee is one of Brazil's main exports.
